_source.message:
üí• SUMMARY üí• Donna Brandenburg's live Rumble with Logik & Jason, His Hard Line, Fri Sept 30 Pt 1/2

1. First, I did listen to Jason's podcast from this morning with Donna, but while I had my hands busy doing other things, so I didn't take notes! Those two got goofy near the end, but they did talk about some interesting things before moving over to her show: https://t.me/HisHardLineShow/1846

2. Censorship: Donna has also posted about being censored by YouTube. Poor Jason gets hit the worst when they try to do shows together; his computer goes bonkers. No, that's not a coincidence. Logik also had issues on this program. Certain topics seem to be triggers. ü§∑‚Äç‚ôÄ

3. This is a good one if you're new to either Logik or Jason, because they asked each other for brief intros and that was nice.

4. They talked a lot about Barclay again. He airs propaganda--not true fair journalism, she says. Trump was supposed to be on his show this morning because he is coming to MI tomorrow. I haven't heard of he was yet.

5. Regarding the "endorsement" by Trump for Dixon, Donna believes Trump is using it as a teaching tool. I totally agree. We didn't have to choose shots because he said so, nor candidates. We shouldn't place our sole trust in endorsements or parties, but learn to discern for ourselves!

I also did some posts on Sept 22 on the "endorsements". I reposted them this morning: 

https://t.me/KarentheRiveter/68356

6. Things will be radically different on MI government under Donna, she says.

7. Logik was speaking bluntly about Melissa Carone. She isn't talking, and letting Eric Castiglia (who she used to speak out against) speak for her now? This doesn't make sense. He agrees she was likely threatened, but he is not allowing her to be excused from his criticisms for it.

She made a live video last night (I haven't seen that yet either), which really ticked him off, Logik said. She's not strong enough to be in the role she accepted (and has sonce denied), but she's doubling down on her lies. He also talked about how she wanted a Trump endorsement and that others tried to manipulate her for it.

8. Donna spoke of loyalty as a core trait. She mentioned that Michael Rothchild once threatened her on Twitter. She reported it to the app and the Secret Service. She also mentioned armed people following her and trying to get her alone to threaten or possibly harm her.

9. Logik- most people don't know what Nazis look like. Sometimes they wear suits and ties and do nice things for their communities. They know the Bible, too, but fake godliness is a real thing.

10. They also promote fear and the lack of desire to think for yourself. Jason started to say, "The Bible says 365 times...", and when he got cut off, Logik didn't skip a beat! He answered, "...do not fear." They laughed because Jason kept getting dropped, proving interference, which is frustrating for him, though. Logik also got dropped sometimes, so Donna closed in prayer.

At one point, Donna said, "I'm the only one left standing." üòÑ I think that won't be the last time we hear her say that. üòâ

11. She spent some time talking about food production, how farmers are being forced to go more local and use more natural approaches, and how a half acre plot could feed 9 families with chickens, 2 goats and produce. üí™

12. "What is real?" Dixon has no real resume. How can we expect her to do what's right when she hasn't done anything thus far? People want the "positions" of candidates, but that is artificial and foolish, because WE are supposed to be telling them what OUR positions are. Their job is to tell us how they'll do it.

13. My notes are not clear, because I listened to part of it late live and the whole again later while multitasking again. Sigh. But next, I have Donna saying, "Michigan has the best elections money can buy!" üòÑüòÑüòÑü§°ü§°ü§°
